## Amendment (PR #7103 review — @drtangible)

Addressed TS-SDK review comments (Python side unchanged):
- Removed `applyIntegrationMetadata` + its 2 unit tests: no production caller in
  TS (only self-tested). Python keeps `apply_integration_metadata` (used by the
  langchain callback) — intentional cross-SDK divergence per the reviewer + user.
- `interface` -> `type` for `IntegrationMetadata` and `IntegrationAttributes`
  (reviewer style pref). Both stay exported: `declaration: true` needs
  `IntegrationAttributes` as `asAttributes`' return type (else TS4053), and the
  test imports `IntegrationMetadata`.
- `INTEGRATION_ATTRIBUTE_KEY`: dropped `export` (used only in-file) and `as const`
  (a `const` string literal is already a literal type; the computed key still
  satisfies the type — confirmed by typecheck:cjs/esm).
- Aliased `import {packageVersion as weavePackageVersion}` to disambiguate from
  `libraryIntegration`'s `packageVersion` option.
- Tightened anthropic.test.ts: dropped optional-chaining guards, assert the whole
  `integration` block. `version` matched via `expect.any(String)` because
  packageVersion is rewritten on every release (a pinned snapshot would break
  each bump) — chosen over the reviewer's `toMatchInlineSnapshot` suggestion for
  that reason.
- KEPT `integration.version` (reviewer asked if it duplicates
  `weave.client_version`): they answer different provenance questions
  (emitting-SDK vs integration-code version), only coincidentally equal for
  first-party integrations, and Python carries it too (trace server reconstructs
  one shape from both SDKs).

